üìä Power BI Dashboard ‚Äì 3-Year Business Analysis (2003‚Äì2005)
An end-to-end Power BI project focused on delivering actionable insights into sales and profit trends over a 3-year period using advanced BI techniques.

üîß Workflow Overview
Data Cleaning & Transformation
Removed duplicates, null values, and formatting inconsistencies.
Standardized columns and converted data types for accuracy.
Parsed date fields to extract Year, Month, Quarter, and Day.
Data Filtering & Pre-processing
Filtered data based on relevant fields: city, employee number, product category, etc.
Created custom columns and measures using DAX for dynamic analysis.
Implemented conditional logic to enhance insight accuracy.
Data Modeling & Relationships
Designed a star schema model for optimal performance.
Established one-to-many and many-to-one relationships between fact and dimension tables.
Managed relationship cardinality and cross-filter direction for precise drill-downs.
Interactive Dashboard Development
Built a visually engaging and interactive Power BI dashboard with:
KPI Cards for Total Sales, Profit, Quantity Ordered
Bar, Column, Line, Area, and Pie Charts
Advanced Slicers for filtering by Year, Month, City, Quarter, Employee Number
Implemented tooltips, bookmarks, and dynamic titles for better user experience.

üí° Insights Delivered
Top & Bottom Selling Products across all dimensions
Most Ordered Categories by Year, Quarter, and Month
Sales Trend Analysis by Day, Month, and Year
Performance Breakdown by City and Employee
Quarterly & Monthly Profitability Patterns
Identified sales peaks and gaps for strategic planning

